# i18n for user-facing strings

Never hardcode user-visible copy in Korean, English, or any language in client UI.

## Required pattern

```tsx
import { useTranslation } from 'react-i18next';
// or: import { useAppTranslation } from '../hooks/useAppTranslation.js';

const { t } = useTranslation('nav'); // pick namespace
return <span>{t('dock.home')}</span>;
```

## Namespaces (`shared/i18n/loadResources.ts`)

| Namespace | Use for |
|-----------|---------|
| `common` | Buttons, errors, resources, connection status |
| `nav` | Dock, header, quick menu |
| `auth` | Login, register, nickname |
| `footer` | Footer, legal links |
| `gameModes` | Game mode display names |
| `game` | In-game controls, turn labels |
| `settings` | Settings modal |

## Adding / updating copy

1. Add keys to **`shared/i18n/catalog/ko.json`** (source) and **`shared/i18n/catalog/en.json`** under the correct namespace.
2. Run **`npm run i18n:translate`** to auto-translate all languages from Korean (writes `catalog/generated/{locale}.json`).
3. Run **`npm run i18n:sync`** to copy masters/generated into `shared/i18n/locales/*.json`.
4. Or one step: **`npm run i18n:build`** (translate + sync).
5. Register new languages in **`shared/i18n/languages.ts`** and **`scripts/i18n/sync-locales.mjs`**, then run i18n:build.

## Helpers

- `translateGameMode(mode)` / `useLocalizedGameMode()` — game mode labels
- `translateQuickUtilityPanel(kind)` / `useLocalizedQuickUtilityPanel()` — quick menu titles
- `components/i18n/LanguageSelect.tsx` — language dropdown in settings

## Exceptions

- Server error messages returned from API (translate on client when displayed, or use error codes)
- User-generated content (chat, nicknames)
- Legal document body text (separate legal namespace / CMS later)
- Developer-only logs
